# Runtime arguments for ds4-server on macOS (Metal).
#
# install.sh reads DS4_SERVER_ARGS, expands each whitespace-separated token into
# one <string> in the LaunchAgent plist's ProgramArguments, and installs the
# result. To change flags later: edit this file (or the copy install.sh made),
# then re-run ./install.sh — it rewrites the plist and reloads the agent.
#
# host 127.0.0.1 keeps the API local-only. 0.0.0.0 exposes it on the LAN; the
# server has NO auth, so firewall the port and only do this on a trusted network.
#
# Paths: -m and --mtp are relative to WORKDIR (the checkout root). The main model
# has a ds4flash.gguf symlink at the root, but download_model.sh writes the MTP
# draft into gguf/, so its path needs that prefix. --kv-disk-dir is absolute.

DS4_SERVER_ARGS="--metal -m ds4flash.gguf --ctx 131072 --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --kv-disk-dir __KVDIR__ --kv-disk-space-mb 8192"

# Optional speculative decoding: append the MTP draft model (path relative to the
# checkout root — it lives under gguf/), e.g.
#   --mtp gguf/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-MTP-Q4K-Q8_0-F32.gguf --mtp-draft 2
#
# MTP helps predictable output (code, structured lists); on divergent free-form
# text the draft-acceptance rate is low and it can be marginally slower.
